<div id="review_1347833152" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1347833152" />
    <a title="Cathleen Dungy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18239769-cathleen-dungy"><img alt="Cathleen Dungy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1498254449p2/18239769.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1347833152?book_show_action=true">Jul 28, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cathleen Dungy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cathleen Dungy" href="/user/show/18239769-cathleen-dungy">Cathleen Dungy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/18946565-the-sublime-transformation-of-vera-wright">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1347833152" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5648661134123012110"><strong>Very Entertaining and Food For the Soul!</strong><br/><br/>I enjoyed this book because it reminded me of my own struggle with discernment and recognizing my own purpose in life. It does take a surprising turn that I didn&apos;t see coming and at times felt a bit outrageous, but in the end it overwhelmed me with messages and things to ponder as I continue in this thing called life. <br/><br/>This along with the author&apos;s other novel &quot;Mystic Tea&quot; is based on characters in the Catholic faith, but this novel is for anyone looking for</span>
  <span id="freeText5648661134123012110" style="display:none"><strong>Very Entertaining and Food For the Soul!</strong><br /><br />I enjoyed this book because it reminded me of my own struggle with discernment and recognizing my own purpose in life. It does take a surprising turn that I didn't see coming and at times felt a bit outrageous, but in the end it overwhelmed me with messages and things to ponder as I continue in this thing called life. <br /><br />This along with the author's other novel "Mystic Tea" is based on characters in the Catholic faith, but this novel is for anyone looking for a good Christian message nestled in a well written body of fiction that will surely enlighten, entertain, and brighten the light within! <br /><br />I gave this book five stars because I enjoyed the author's descriptions and development of the characters and her use of the Lords message. </span>
